<TITLE> EC to ask CA on Sept 11 to lift indoor politics ban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com)  The Election Commission will ask chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed on September 11 to open the door to indoor politics, the chief election commissioner said Sunday. "We are expecting to hold dialogues on electoral reforms with political parties on Sept 12," ATM Shamsul Huda told reporters at his office. "If the ban on indoor politics is not lifted we will meet the chief adviser on Sept 11 and request him to allow it." "We need to know the government decision on indoor politics," Huda said. "If any party fails to have dialogue on schedule [it] can defer the time in discussion with the commission." "We want meaningful discussion." "The reforms we have made proposed to electoral law is long-lasting and significant. These things should be discussed in party forum," the chief election commissioner said. On April 4, the CEC met law adviser Mainul Hosein and asked him to lift restrictions on indoor politics. bdnews24.
